subSubSection.paragraph:
Collophore. Anterior side with 22 chaetae, 12 proximal spine-like chaetae, 3 ciliated chaetae, 5 ciliated chaetae apically acuminate and 2 mac distally; posterior side with 11 chaetae, 9 thin ciliated chaetae widely distributed and 1 ciliated and 1 smooth chaetae distally; lateral flap with about 42 chaetae, 11 smooth and 31 ciliated (
Fig. 49E
).

Furcula. Manubrium ventral formula with 1, 2 2, 2/2 (subapical), 2/16 (apical) ciliated chaetae of different sizes plus approximately 15 elongated apical scales per side (
Fig. 49F
); manubrial plate with 3 blunt mac weakly ciliated abruptly acuminate at the apex, 6 ciliated chaetae of different sizes and 3 psp. Dens dorsally with 9 blunt mac finely ciliated and apically nipple-like (
Fig. 49G
).
